ion for lambda functions and whether their metadata will be accessible. The `writeReplace` might work but could throw errors if it relies on private methods without registration. I’m also pondering if the class names of dynamically generated lambdas are stable after the compile order and how Graal handles lambda serialization. Perhaps I should search the repository for tests on serializable lambdas to clarify how they're treated.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_YNKlR3gtEr19kw4gNlHPso77|fc_0267f174ab6605d20169fb2037dda881a2a32df1a8a8f84794", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"SerializedLambda|Serializable.*Supplier|writeReplace|LineNumbers\" tests/src -g '*.scala' -g '*.java' | head -100"}, "partialJson": "{\"command\":\"rg \\\"SerializedLambda|Serializable.*Supplier|writeReplace|LineNumbers\\\" tests/src -g '*.scala' -g '*.java' | head -100\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 370, "output": 941, "cacheRead": 25600, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26911, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778065447728, "responseId": "resp_0267f174ab6605d20169fb20288f4081a29b787324c17e3e16"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_YNKlR3gtEr19kw4gNlHPso77|fc_0267f174ab6605d20169fb2037dda881a2a32df1a8a8f84794", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/org.immutables/value/2.8.2/src/test/java/org_immutables/value/MultimapsCustomSetMultimapTest.java:                new SerializableLinkedHashSetSupplier<>()\ntests/src/org.immutables/value/2.8.2/src/test/java/org_immutables/value/MultimapsCustomSetMultimapTest.java:    private static final class SerializableLinkedHashSetSupplier<T> implements $Supplier<Set<T>>, Serializable {\ntests/src/org.immutables/value/2.8.6/src/test/java/org_immutables/value/MultimapsCustomSetMultimapTest.java:                new SerializableLinkedHashSetSupplie